    "recap_headline": "Grand Canyon University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Grand Canyon dropped its weekend opener to Rice 16-5 on Friday night at Brazell Field at GCU Ballpark despite several productive offensive performances from the Lopes lineup.\nRice (11-8) used early offense with three runs in the first and four in the second to build a lead it would not relinquish, finishing with 16 hits and 10 walks in the win.\nGCU (6-12) showed offensive flashes throughout the night, beginning with a run in the first inning before adding two in the fifth and two more in the sixth.\nSophomore second baseman\nJake Sanko\nled the Lopes with a 2-for-4 performance and two runs scored, while junior right fielder\nBilly Scaldeferri\nwent 2 for 4 with an RBI triple. Senior designated hitter\nDominic Chacon\nalso delivered a bright spot with a solo home run in the sixth inning, his third of the season.\nGraduate catcher\nMito Perez\n, junior first baseman\nCannon Peery\nand junior shortstop\nTroy Sanders\neach added a hit as the Lopes totaled nine hits and drew seven walks, but GCU struggled to convert scoring opportunities, finishing 1 for 13 with runners in scoring position and leaving 12 runners on base.\nJunior right-hander\nGarrett Ahern\ntook the loss after starting the game for GCU, while the Lopes bullpen combined to cover the final 5 1/3 innings. Senior righty\nBrock Toney\nprovided a clean inning in relief in the eighth, striking out one and allowing no baserunners.\nGCU will quickly get back to the diamond with a pair of games on Saturday. The Lopes will play Saint Mary's at 1 p.m. and rematch with Rice at 6 p.m."
  },
